==Old English==
===Etymology===
West Germanic *''xerþaz'', from Germanic ''*xer-'' ‘burn, fire’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[herth]], Old Saxon [[herþ]] (Dutch [[haard]]), Old High German [[hert]] (German [[Herd]]); the Germanic root is also reflected in Old Norse [[hyrr]] ‘fire’, Gothic [[𐌷𐌰𐌿𐍂𐌹]] ‘coal’.

